# File Organization

## Directory Structure
```
components/
  ├── layout/          # Layout components (header, footer, navigation)
  ├── sections/        # Page sections (hero, about, skills, etc.)
  └── ui/              # Reusable UI components

hooks/                 # Custom React hooks
constants/             # Constants and configuration
lib/                   # Utility functions and helpers
types/                 # TypeScript type definitions
data/                  # Static data (content.json)
tests/                 # Test files
```

## File Naming
- **Components**: PascalCase (e.g., `Hero.tsx`, `ProjectCard.tsx`)
- **Hooks**: camelCase with `use` prefix (e.g., `useNavigation.ts`, `useScrollUrlSync.ts`)
- **Utilities**: camelCase (e.g., `utils.ts`, `logger.ts`)
- **Constants**: camelCase (e.g., `sections.ts`, `config.ts`)
- **Types**: camelCase (e.g., `content.ts`)
- **Directories**: kebab-case (e.g., `project-card/`, `timeline-item/`)

## File Locations
- **Components**: `components/` directory
  - Sections: `components/sections/{section-name}/`
  - UI components: `components/ui/{component-name}/` or `components/ui/{component-name}.tsx`
  - Layout: `components/layout/{layout-name}/`
- **Hooks**: `hooks/` directory at root level
- **Constants**: `constants/` directory, exported via `constants/index.ts`
- **Types**: `types/` directory
- **Utilities**: `lib/` directory
- **Data**: `data/` directory

## Test Organization
- Mirror source structure in `tests/` directory
- Use descriptive test file names: `{component}.test.tsx` or `{utility}.test.ts`
- Group related tests with `describe` blocks
